review_text: Best Mark s I went into so far, organized, clean and spacious, parking and strategic location for one time stop, staff are professional and helpful, when it s busy everyone jumps to cash so we don t wait in the line, fitting rooms are always open and clean, comparing it to last year the same time holy big difference!!

Bought a pair of steel toe shoes for work just under 3 months ago and soles were separating from the rest of the shoe. Lost my receipt but figured Id go in and ask, worst theyd say is sorry. Was also hoping they could look up the receipt as my work reimburses. Unfortunately they arent able to look up old receipts, which was a shame, but the employees that I spoke to were very nice about it. They took me at my word that Id purchased the shoes within 3 months and allowed me to exchange them with a new pair due to manufacturers defect. Do recommend as it was a pleasant experience. review_text: Great selection, wasnt busy, and staff said hello shortly after we entered. Have shopped here 1/2 a doz times over the last couple years, and I will go back again.

Marks Work Wearhouse (And why you should shop there!) About a year ago I was diagnosed with Type 2 Diabetes. I had just purchased 4 mens dress shirts, size XXL relaxed fit. I wore one shirt, and the remaining 3 shirts sat in the drawer unopened. I have spent the last 10+ months eating healthy (Keto Lifestyle) and exercising daily. I routinely walk a minimum of 8 kilometers per day, and up to 20 - 30 kilometers on Saturdays and Sundays . . . rain, snow, or shine. I have recently got back on my road bike as well. As a result, my body size has reduced dramatically. I now wear a mens L or XL, slim fit and my waist is now 32.5 (down from 44) I contacted Marks Work Wearhouse in-store to find out if I could exchange the unopened shirts I purchased online. Sadly the store clerk couldnt help me, but she was very nice and apologized. I contacted Marks Work Wearhouse online and within a couple of weeks, smaller sized shirts have arrived on my doorstep. I was told by Marks Work Wearhouse to donate the unopened XXL shirts to charity. The Lady from Marks also congratulated me on my accomplishment. This is a great example of a community oriented company going above and beyond the call. At least for me, they have a satisfied customer for life. This is why I will always shop at Marks Work Wearhouse.
